# Next.js Rules

## Core Principles
- Default to Server Components for better performance
- Minimize `'use client'` directives to leverage SSR benefits
- Use `nuqs` for URL search parameter state management

## Code Style
- **Enforce single-line if statements without brackets**: Use `if(condition) doSomething()` or `condition && doSomething()` for one-liners
- Multi-line if statements must use brackets
- Prefer one-liners for simple conditional logic

## Server vs Client Components
- Favor Server Components and Next.js SSR
- Use client components only when necessary (interactive UI, browser APIs)

## Performance Optimization
- Implement streaming with `Suspense` for progressive loading
- Optimize Core Web Vitals:
  - Largest Contentful Paint (LCP) < 2.5s
  - First Input Delay (FID) < 100ms
  - Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS) < 0.1
- Optimize images:
  - Use WebP format
  - Include proper size data
  - Implement lazy loading for below-fold images

## Server Actions
